[src:lombok-java-lib/java-programming-language] Java 11, but removed as of Java 16) allowing tiered compilation.
[src:lombok-java-lib/java-programming-language] Java itself is platform-independent and is adapted to the particular platform it is to run on by a Java virtual machine (JVM), which translates the JVM bytecode into the platform's machine language.
[src:lombok-java-lib/java-programming-language] Programs written in Java have a reputation for being slower and requiring more memory than those written in C++.
